prvtEfmOamMIB.name: prvtEfmOamMIB
prvtEfmOamMIB.contactinfo: BATM/Telco Systems Support team Email: For North America: techsupport@telco.com For North Europe: support@batm.de, info@batm.de For the rest of the world: techsupport@telco.com
prvtEfmOamMIB.description: This MIB should provide general configuration and reports of this protocol that are not available in the standard DOT3-OAM-MIB, such as Enabling and Timers, as well as the ability to control private extensions added to the EFM OAM.

prvtEfmOamEnable.name: prvtEfmOamEnable
prvtEfmOamEnable.description: Enable/disable the EFM OAM on the device

prvtEfmOamMultiPduCount.name: prvtEfmOamMultiPduCount
prvtEfmOamMultiPduCount.description: Number of OAM PDUs that will be sent when protocol ask to send multiple subsequent messages.

prvtEfmOamRemoteEvent.name: prvtEfmOamRemoteEvent
prvtEfmOamRemoteEvent.description: Enable or disable sending the local event notifications to the remote device.

prvtEfmOamLogEvents.name: prvtEfmOamLogEvents
prvtEfmOamLogEvents.description: Disable/enable sending of Event Notification OAM PDU to the local Syslog daemon.

prvtEfmOamPriority.name: prvtEfmOamPriority
prvtEfmOamPriority.description: Priority of the sent OAM PDUs.

prvtEfmOamKeepAliveInterval.name: prvtEfmOamKeepAliveInterval
prvtEfmOamKeepAliveInterval.description: Aging interval (in miliseconds)of the last heard neighbouring device.

prvtEfmOamHelloInterval.name: prvtEfmOamHelloInterval
prvtEfmOamHelloInterval.description: Maximal interval between a pair of PDUs in milliseconds.

prvtEfmOamHistoryLimit.name: prvtEfmOamHistoryLimit
prvtEfmOamHistoryLimit.description: Number of entries in EFM_OAM history.

prvtEfmOamHistoryCount.name: prvtEfmOamHistoryCount
prvtEfmOamHistoryCount.description: Number of entries in efm-oam history.

prvtEfmOamPingTable.name: prvtEfmOamPingTable
prvtEfmOamPingTable.description: This table let the EFM-OAM non-intrusive monitoring on the specific interface by querying a number of time aFramesTransmittedOK parameter, ping requests, using the variable retrieval EFM OAM PDU. Ping operation procedure: 1. Set prvtEfmOamPingRowStatus to CreateandWait 2. Configure parameters that are different from default 3. Set prvtEfmOamPingStatus to startPing 4. Set prvtEfmOamPingRowStatus to Active to start the operation. If the operation is performed from cli, at the end prvtEfmOamPingStatus is set to stopPing and if is perfomed from SNMP prvtEfmOamPingStatus is set to startPing.

prvtEfmOamPingEchoNumber.name: prvtEfmOamPingEchoNumber
prvtEfmOamPingEchoNumber.description: The number of echo packets to send.

prvtEfmOamPingDelayTime.name: prvtEfmOamPingDelayTime
prvtEfmOamPingDelayTime.description: The delay in seconds between packets.

prvtEfmOamPingTimeOut.name: prvtEfmOamPingTimeOut
prvtEfmOamPingTimeOut.description: The time in seconds which the ping should wait for the response.

prvtEfmOamPingResultClear.name: prvtEfmOamPingResultClear
prvtEfmOamPingResultClear.description: Delete per interface entries in prvtEfmOamPingResultTable.

prvtEfmOamLoopbackTable.name: prvtEfmOamLoopbackTable
prvtEfmOamLoopbackTable.description: This table should permit to perform EFM-OAM intrusive monitoring on the specific interface by setting the remote device into loopback state and generating test traffic. It should support: Storm operation, an operation that sets remote loopback, stops local data flow to the remote box and generates a packet burst by CPU. When the burst is received back it is validated and statistics are displayed. Burst operation, an operation that sets remote loopback, stops local data flow to the remote box and generates a packet test burst by the hardware (when available). It means a single packet generated by CPU is repetitively sent by the hardware. When the burst is received back it is ignored and only counters are displayed. Loopback storm operation procedure: 1. Set prvtEfmOamLoopbackRowStatus to CreateandWait 2. Configure prvtEfmOamLoopbackType to set the operation 3. Configure other parameters that are different from default 4. Set prvtEfmOamLoopbackStatus to initiatingLoopback 5. Set prvtEfmOamLoopbackRowStatus to Active to start the operation. If the operation is performed from cli, at the end prvtEfmOamLoopbackStatus is set to terminatingLoopback and if is perfomed from SNMP prvtEfmOamLoopbackStatus is set to initiatingLoopback.

prvtEfmOamLoopbackCount.name: prvtEfmOamLoopbackCount
prvtEfmOamLoopbackCount.description: Represent the count of packets to send in storm operation.

prvtEfmOamLoopbackPacketSize.name: prvtEfmOamLoopbackPacketSize
prvtEfmOamLoopbackPacketSize.description: Represent the size of the test packet to use.

prvtEfmOamLoopbackDelay.name: prvtEfmOamLoopbackDelay
prvtEfmOamLoopbackDelay.description: Represent the delay between packets in seconds. The default value is 0 and represents no delay.

prvtEfmOamLoopbackTimeout.name: prvtEfmOamLoopbackTimeout
prvtEfmOamLoopbackTimeout.description: Represent the wait for response in seconds.

prvtEfmOamLoopbackResultsClear.name: prvtEfmOamLoopbackResultsClear
prvtEfmOamLoopbackResultsClear.description: Clear loopback results for this ifIndex.

prvtEfmOamPeerTable.name: prvtEfmOamPeerTable
prvtEfmOamPeerTable.description: This table holds the peer extended information available only when local interface is set in enhanced mode (see prvtOamEnhanceMode) and the remote is detected as enhanced-mode device. This table shall containg an entry per physical interface, indexed by the corresponding ifIndex from IF-MIB.

prvtEfmOamEventConfigTable.name: prvtEfmOamEventConfigTable
prvtEfmOamEventConfigTable.description: Enable Event Notifications and configure the thresholds.

prvtEfmOamEventConfigEntry.name: prvtEfmOamEventConfigEntry
prvtEfmOamEventConfigEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface

prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodWi.name: prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodWindow
prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodWi.description: If prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodThreshold symbol errors occur within a window of prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodWindow symbols, an Event Notification OAMPDU should be generated with an Errored Symbol Period Event TLV indicating that the threshold has been crossed in this window.

prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodTh.name: prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodThreshold
prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodTh.description: If prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodThreshold symbol errors occur within a window of prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodWindow symbols, an Event Notification OAMPDU should be generated with an Errored Symbol Period Event TLV indicating that the threshold has been crossed in this window.

prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodEv.name: prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodEventNotificationEnable
prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorSymbolPeriodEv.description: If true, the OAM entity should send an Event Notification OAMPDU when an Errored Symbol Period Event occurs.

prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorFrameWindow.name: prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorFrameWindow
prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorFrameWindow.description: Symbol period monitor interval in seconds

prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorFrameThreshold.name: prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorFrameThreshold
prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorFrameThreshold.description: The amount of time over which the threshold is defined.

prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorFrameEventNoti.name: prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorFrameEventNotificationEnable
prvtEfmOamEventConfigErrorFrameEventNoti.description: If true, the OAM entity should send an Event Notification OAMPDU when an Errored Frame Event occurs

prvtEfmOamEventConfigDyingGaspEnable.name: prvtEfmOamEventConfigDyingGaspEnable
prvtEfmOamEventConfigDyingGaspEnable.description: If true, the local OAM entity should attempt to indicate a dying gasp via the OAMPDU flags field to its peer OAM entity when a dying gasp event occurs.

prvtEfmOamInterfaceEventReturnShutdown.name: prvtEfmOamInterfaceEventReturnShutdown
prvtEfmOamInterfaceEventReturnShutdown.description: The number of handshaking attempts before shutting down the port (value 0 disable it).

prvtEfmOamEventForwardStatusIdx.name: prvtEfmOamEventForwardStatusIdx
prvtEfmOamEventForwardStatusIdx.description: Interface to which status will be forwarded

prvtEfmOamEventForwardShutdownIdx.name: prvtEfmOamEventForwardShutdownIdx
prvtEfmOamEventForwardShutdownIdx.description: Interface to which status will be forwarded

prvtEfmOamLoopBackState.name: prvtEfmOamLoopBackState
prvtEfmOamLoopBackState.description: This trap should be sent whenever the loopback state has been change from remote, when prvtEfmOamInterfaceRole is passive or prvtEfmOamInterfaceEnable is false the interface cannot be on remoteLoopback state and should send this trap.

prvtEfmOamDyingGasp.name: prvtEfmOamDyingGasp
prvtEfmOamDyingGasp.description: The notification alarms for a failure due to loss of local power - Dying Gasp

prvtEfmOamThresholdEvent.name: prvtEfmOamThresholdEvent
prvtEfmOamThresholdEvent.description: A prvtEfmOamThresholdEvent notification is sent when a local or remote threshold crossing event is detected. A local threshold crossing event is detected by the local entity, while a remote threshold crossing event is detected by the reception of an Ethernet OAM Event Notification OAMPDU that indicates a threshold event. The OAM entity can be derived from extracting the ifIndex from the variable bindings. The objects in the notification correspond to the values in a row instance in the prvtEfmOamEventLogTable. The management entity should periodically check prvtEfmOamEventLogTable to detect any missed events.

prvtEfmOamNonThresholdEvent.name: prvtEfmOamNonThresholdEvent
prvtEfmOamNonThresholdEvent.description: A prvtEfmOamNonThresholdEvent notification is sent when a local or remote non-threshold crossing event is detected. A local event is detected by the local entity, while a remote event is detected by the reception of an Ethernet OAM Event Notification OAMPDU that indicates a non-threshold crossing event. The OAM entity can be derived from extracting the ifIndex from the variable bindings. The objects in the notification correspond to the values in a row instance of the prvtEfmOamEventLogTable. The management entity should periodically check prvtEfmOamEventLogTable to detect any missed events.
